Chapter 4 is very short and has a lot of exposition, but still leaves us with more questions. The plot thickens, whichever way your suspicions go. Once again, the puzzles are challenging enough to leave us wondering for a bit, but never completely stuck. And the artwork is brilliant as ever. I'm sad to have only one chapter left, and at the same time thrilled to play the finale.

Little Fran managed pull on my heart strings while guiding her through a plethora of areas, problems, and adventures. Now that we've parted ways, she and her friends hold a special place in my heart. The characters are lovable and varying which makes this game a real joy to play. The art is a visual treasure that just keeps getting better each iterarion. My only complaint is the game has ended and I find myself still wanting more!
